re%20complex%20or%20crucial%20issues%20are%20overlooked%2C%26quot%3B%20%C3%96zdemir%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20comes%20from%20the%20idea%20that%20people%20will%20debate%20the%20color%20of%20a%20bike%20shed%20while%20ignoring%20the%20design%20of%20the%20nuclear%20power%20plant%20it's%20meant%20to%20house.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22ded81fe9-acc9-4d8b-bd7a-fd2c6519d401%5C%22%3E3.%20%3Cstrong%3EBoilerplate%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBoilerplate%20refers%20to%20sections%20of%20code%20that%20have%20to%20be%20included%20in%20many%20places%20with%20little%20or%20no%20alteration.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20often%20seen%20as%20a%20necessary%20evil%20and%20a%20potential%20place%20for%20future%20optimization%2C%26quot%3B%20%C3%96zdemir%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22a6301b1c-4660-4419-b5e6-cf54f6924d54%5C%22%3E4.%20%3Cstrong%3ESpaghetti%20code%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%C3%96zdemir%20described%20spaghetti%20code%20as%20a%20disparaging%20term%20for%20software%20with%20a%20complex%20and%20tangled%20control%20structure%20%E2%80%94%20especially%20one%20using%20many%20GOTO%20statements%2C%20exceptions%2C%20threads%2C%20or%20other%20unstructured%20branching%20constructs.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20a%20nightmare%20to%20read%2C%20debug%2C%20and%20maintain%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2273cecebd-c760-4257-a70d-fccc20ec808f%5C%22%3E5.%20%3Cstrong%3EEaster%20egg%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAn%20Easter%20egg%20in%20software%20engineering%20refers%20to%20a%20hidden%20feature%20or%20novelty%20the%20programmers%20have%20put%20in%20their%20software.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22d8934d3c-b199-40fb-b52b-a0d582369dd4%5C%22%3E6.%20%3Cstrong%3ERefactoring%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20process%20of%20rewriting%20existing%20code%20to%20improve%20its%20readability%2C%20structure%2C%20or%20performance%20without%20changing%20its%20behavior%20is%20known%20as%20refactoring.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20like%20tidying%20up%20your%20room%2C%26quot%3B%20%C3%96zdemir%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt%20doesn't%20make%20it%20any%20bigger%2C%20but%20it%20does%20make%20it%20easier%20to%20navigate.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EKomal%20Fatima%20has%20a%20BS%20in%20computer%20software%20engineering%20and%20a%20master's%20in%20computer%20software%20technology.%20She%20currently%20works%20at%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fgaper.io%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGaper%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20hires%20remote%20software%20engineers%2C%20as%20a%20senior%20SEO%20manager.%20Although%20she%20is%20fairly%20new%20to%20the%20tech%20industry%2C%20with%20three%20years%20under%20her%20belt%2C%20she's%20had%20a%20crash%20course%20in%20the%20lingo.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFatima's%20list%20includes%20rubber%20duck%20and%20bikeshedding%20as%20well%2C%20and%20she%20added%20these%20three%20industry%20slang%20terms%20and%20definitions%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22ad7fc23d-f50c-4678-9f73-515e7fe6e629%5C%22%3E7.%20%3Cstrong%3ECode%20smell%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ECode%20smell%20is%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Epoorly%20written%20or%20structured%20code%20that%20may%20contain%20bugs%20or%20inefficiencies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22b4a12394-5151-4a63-82c1-b0ab335974f8%5C%22%3E8.%20%3Cstrong%3EYak%20shaving%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EGetting%20sidetracked%20by%20unrelated%20tasks%20before%20addressing%20the%20original%20problem%20is%20also%20known%20as%20yak%20shaving.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22a92b8397-1486-4948-b764-7e35e7701a58%5C%22%3E9.%20%3Cstrong%3ELegacy%20code%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOlder%2C%20often%20outdated%2C%20software%20that%20requires%20maintenance%20and%20lacks%20proper%20documentation%20is%20called%20legacy%20code.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20are%20so%20many%20slang%20terms%20which%20are%20specific%20to%20the%20software%20industry%2C%20I%20think%20it's%20impossible%20to%20exhaustively%20list%20them%20all%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Abhinav%20Upadhya%2C%20a%20seasoned%20engineer%20with%20expertise%20in%20robotics%20and%20automation%20who%20has%20a%20decade%20of%20industry%20experience%20and%20is%20currently%20a%20senior%20engineer%20at%20L%26amp%3BT%20Technology%20Services%20Limited.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUpadhyay%20founded%20the%20podcast%20search%20engine%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdrpawd.substack.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EDrPawd%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20writes%20about%20programming%20in%20the%20newsletter%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcodeconfessions.substack.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EConfessions%20of%20a%20Code%20Addict%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHis%20list%20of%20terms%20for%20software%20industry%20newbies%20includes%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22fe03f175-348a-4919-b2eb-1062f7df37c8%5C%22%3E10.%20%3Cstrong%3EDuck%20typing%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAlso%20called%20dynamically%20typed%20languages%2C%20duck%20typing%20refers%20to%20a%20class%20of%20programming%20languages%20that%20don't%20have%20strict%20typing.%20%26quot%3BBasically%2C%20this%20means%20that%20if%20an%20object%20behaves%20like%20a%20duck%2C%20then%20it%20is%20probably%20a%20duck%2C%20but%20the%20language%20will%20not%20ensure%20or%20enforce%20that%20it%20is%20actually%20a%20duck%2C%26quot%3B%20Upadhyay%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSuch%20loose%20requirements%20make%20it%20easier%20to%20churn%20out%20code%2C%20however%2C%20at%20the%20cost%20of%20potential%20bugs%20and%20code%20readability.%26quot%3B%20He%20added%20that%20many%20companies%20use%20these%20languages%2C%20such%20as%20Python%2C%20Ruby%2C%20and%20JavaScript%2C%20to%20name%20a%20few.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2292ce7ca8-e24e-43c1-aaf4-0756e7f1804f%5C%22%3E11.%20%3Cstrong%3EBare%20metal%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBare%20metal%2C%20according%20to%20Upadhyay%2C%20usually%20refers%20to%20running%20the%20code%20directly%20on%20the%20hardware%20without%20using%20any%20virtualization%20or%20abstraction%20layers%20between%20the%20code%20and%20the%20hardware.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20commonly%20used%20in%20the%20embedded%20systems%20world%2C%20and%20if%20you%20decide%20to%20work%20in%20that%20domain%2C%20you%20should%20know%20this%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2249dd584a-0039-4263-b2dc-a8202440824b%5C%22%3E12.%20%3Cstrong%3ERTFM%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ERTFM%20stands%20for%20%26quot%3BRead%20the%20Fucking%20Manual.%26quot%3B%20%26quot%3BThis%20is%20an%20old%20acronym%2C%20and%20you'll%20hear%20old-timers%20using%20this%20to%20point%20newcomers%20toward%20reading%20the%20documentation%20before%20asking%20questions%2C%26quot%3B%20Upadhyay%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%221657a3c5-ec57-40b1-9101-1ec474ab4442%5C%22%3E13.%20%3Cstrong%3EKISS%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESoftware%20engineers%20use%20another%20common%20acronym%20%E2%80%94%20KISS%2C%20for%20%26quot%3BKeep%20it%20Simple%2C%20Stupid%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20as%20a%20guiding%20principle%20when%20designing%20code.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20idea%20is%20that%20the%20design%20should%20be%20kept%20as%20simple%20as%20possible%20and%20delay%20introducing%20complexity%20as%20late%20as%20possible%2C%26quot%3B%20Upadhyay%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22f102401d-55f2-4fca-9c8a-6b85032a1f18%5C%22%3E14.%20%3Cstrong%3EMagic%20numbers%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EPeople%20often%20need%20to%20use%20hard-coded%20numbers%20as%20parameters%20in%20their%20code%20%E2%80%94%20Upadhyay%20said%20software%20engineers%20refer%20to%20these%20as%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Emagic%20numbers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20usually%20use%20trial%20and%20error%20or%20guessing%20to%20arrive%20at%20good%20values%20for%20these%20numbers%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BHowever%2C%20they%20don't%20have%20a%20good%20explanation%20for%20why%20those%20work.%20Such%20hard-coded%20numbers%20in%20the%20code%20are%20usually%20called%20magic%20numbers%20because%20they%20work%20like%20magic%20as%20no%20one%20understands%20how%20they%20work.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20added%20that%20you%20may%20read%20the%20phrase%20magic%20number%20in%20industry%20textbooks%20or%20documentation%20and%20hear%20it%20used%20by%20other%20engineers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2235f133a5-99a3-4a96-805c-2d7d512ddeaf%5C%22%3E15.%20%3Cstrong%3EZero-day%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20term%20zero-day%20refers%20to%20a%20security%20vulnerability%20that's%20unknown%20to%20the%20software%20vendor%20or%20developer.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20called%20zero-day%20because%20it's%20being%20actively%20exploited%20in%20the%20wild%20by%20the%20attackers%20before%20the%20developers%20have%20had%20zero%20days%20to%20fix%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20Upadhyay%20said.%20%26quot%3BIf%20working%20in%20the%20computer%20security%20area%2C%20this%20is%20a%20must-know%20term.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsoftware-engineering-slang-terms-phrases-need-to-know-2025-1%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1737108302000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F678951ad10c98eace912b761%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsoftware-engineering-slang-terms-phrases-need-to-know-2025-1%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Business%20Insider%20tapped%20three%20software%20engineers%20to%20share%20the%20slang%20words%20and%20phrases%20incoming%20newbies%20need%20to%20know%20before%20breaking%20in.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Robin%20Madell)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A32%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsoftware-engineering-slang-terms-phrases-need-to-know-2025-1%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Zar%20Amir%2C%20Viggo%20Mortensen%2C%20No%C3%A9mie%20Merlant%20to%20Serve%20on%202025%20MyFrenchFi