ften%20locked%20behind%20strict%20user%20requirements%20that%20align%20with%20Beijing's%20government%20standards.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWeibo%2C%20for%20example%2C%20requires%20all%20users%20to%20register%20with%20their%20full%20names%2C%20and%20the%20app%20displays%20their%20location%20and%20gender%20to%20other%20users.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20TikTok%2C%20founded%20by%20Chinese%20company%20Bytedance%2C%20is%20separate%20from%20China's%20version%20of%20the%20app%2C%20Douyin.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECross-border%20interactions%20on%20RedNote%20have%20been%20mostly%20friendly%2C%20at%20a%20time%20when%20US-China%20tensions%20have%20dominated%20global%20politics.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20so%20amazing%20to%20have%20you%20here%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20one%20Chinese%20user%20in%20a%20viral%20post.%20%26quot%3BFor%20so%20long%2C%20we%20haven't%20been%20able%20to%20connect%20or%20talk%20to%20each%20other%20like%20this.%20But%20now%20we%20finally%20can%2C%20and%20it%20feels%20so%20special.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHis%20video%2C%20titled%20%26quot%3BAmerican%20friends%20please%20stay%20here%2C%26quot%3B%20received%20over%20174%2C000%20likes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20users%20began%20hosting%20%26quot%3Bcultural%20exchange%26quot%3B%20livestream%20audio%20chats%2C%20inviting%20young%20American%20and%20Chinese%20people%20to%20discuss%20their%20lives%20and%20befriend%20each%20other.%20One%20such%20livestream%2C%20seen%20by%20Business%20Insider%2C%20was%20watched%20by%2070%2C000%20users%2C%20with%20hundreds%20tuning%20in%20at%20a%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22e3833cc0-14f6-47c1-b938-60cdc8d3b50d%5C%22%3EToo%20early%20to%20tell%20how%20RedNote%20will%20impact%20US-China%20relations%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EResearchers%20and%20academics%20who%20study%20US-China%20relations%20told%20BI%20they're%20watching%20the%20space%20with%20interest%2C%20but%20that%20it's%20still%20too%20early%20to%20say%20how%20the%20RedNote%20migration%20might%20play%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20it's%20likely%20true%20that%20many%20Chinese%20are%20interacting%20with%20Americans%20for%20the%20first%20time%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Stanley%20Rosen%2C%20a%20professor%20of%20political%20science%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Southern%20California's%20US-China%20Institute.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERosen%20said%20China's%20government%20might%20initially%20be%20pleased%20by%20the%20influx%20of%20American%20users%20to%20RedNote%2C%20given%20how%20Beijing%20has%20criticized%20the%20impending%20ban%20on%20TikTok.%20Congressional%20leaders%20who%20voted%20to%20pass%20the%20divest-or-ban%20law%20against%20ByteDance%20had%20cited%20concerns%20about%20Chinese%20ownership.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20Rosen%20added%20that%20letting%20Chinese%20and%20American%20users%20mingle%20en%20masse%20could%20eventually%20disrupt%20Beijing's%20careful%20governance%20of%20its%20online%20platforms.%20For%20instance%2C%20a%20Chinese%20person's%20complaints%20about%20low%20pay%20could%20be%20met%20with%20well-intentioned%20%E2%80%94%20yet%20potentially%20contentious%20%E2%80%94%20replies%20from%20Americans%2C%20who%20might%20suggest%20forming%20a%20union%20or%20going%20on%20strike%2C%20Rosen%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAmerican%20users%20are%20still%20subject%20to%20Chinese%20rules%20on%20RedNote.%20For%20example%2C%20two%20writers%20from%20the%20entertainment%20news%20site%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thewrap.com%2Fred-note-block-american-users-tiananmen-square-uyghur-posts-tiktok%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20Wrap%3C%2Fa%3E%20reported%20on%20Wednesday%20that%20they%20uploaded%20a%20post%20about%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftiananmen-square-2015-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E1989%20Tiananmen%20Square%20protests%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20a%20heavily%20censored%20topic%20on%20the%20Chinese%20internet%20%E2%80%94%20and%20found%20that%20it%20was%20taken%20down%20within%20five%20minutes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlfred%20Wu%2C%20an%20associate%20professor%20at%20the%20Lee%20Kuan%20Yew%20School%20of%20Public%20Policy%20at%20the%20National%20University%20of%20Singapore%2C%20told%20BI%20that%20it's%20unlikely%20that%20any%20friendly%20interactions%20on%20RedNote%20would%20impact%20US-China%20relations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20tensions%20between%20these%20countries%20are%20based%20on%20very%20long-term%20problems%2C%26quot%3B%20Wu%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20this%20sort%20of%20passion%20will%20die%20very%20soon%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%220ecf3290-668e-4e0f-a619-1acdb32c5467%5C%22%3ERedNote's%20popularity%20may%20not%20last%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20fact%2C%20RedNote's%20newfound%20popularity%20in%20the%20West%20could%20just%20end%20up%20being%20a%20temporary%20phenomenon.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENatalie%20Pang%2C%20an%20associate%20professor%20at%20the%20National%20University%20of%20Singapore's%20department%20of%20communications%20and%20new%20media%2C%20told%20BI%20that%20such%20massive%20user%20migrations%20from%20one%20platform%20to%20another%20haven't%20always%20been%20sustainable.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMany%20years%20ago%2C%20when%20WhatsApp%20announced%20certain%20features%20on%20their%20platform%2C%20people%20also%20left%20WhatsApp%20and%20migrated%20to%20Signal%2C%20but%20those%20migrations%20were%20not%20sustained%2C%26quot%3B%20Pang%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPlatforms%20are%20only%20able%20to%20retain%20these%20new%20users%20if%20their%20network%20moves%20along%20with%20them%2C%20she%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20have%20to%20understand%20that%20these%20'TikTok%20Refugees'%20are%20moving%20to%20Xiaohongshu%20as%20part%20of%20a%20protest%20against%20the%20TikTok%20ban.%20So%20if%20we%20understand%20this%20move%20as%20part%20of%20a%20protest%2C%20then%20I%20think%20we'll%20see%20more%20sustained%20migration%20toward%20the%20platform%20if%20interest%20in%20the%20protest%20continues%2C%26quot%3B%20Pang%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20said%2C%20TikTok%