ot%3Bstupid.%26quot%3B%20He%20assured%20the%20charge%20would%20be%20removed%20and%20corrective%20measures%20would%20be%20taken%20to%20prevent%20such%20mistakes.%20This%20response%20followed%20criticism%20from%20Rohit%20Ranjan%2C%20who%20highlighted%20the%20issue%20on%20LinkedIn%2C%20calling%20the%20charge%20unfair.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22TOI%20NEWS%20DESK%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Opinion%3A%20'Shrinkonomics'%20And%20Why%20India%20Has%20Just%2030%20Years%20To%20Escape%20It%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EFirst%2C%20some%20numbers%20that%20stunned%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20reflecting%20on%20the%20250th%20anniversary%20of%20the%20Boston%20Tea%20Party%2C%20a%20blog%20from%20the%20U.S.%20Census%20Office%20made%20the%20following%20observation%3A%20%E2%80%9CThe%20first%20census%20in%20the%20United%20States%20(1790)%20counted%20almost%204%20million%20residents.%20The%20first%20census%20in%20Great%20Britain%20(1801)%20counted%20almost%2011%20million%20residents.%20Fast%20forward%20to%20today%20when%20according%20to%20the%20Census%20Bureau's%20International%20Database%2C%20the%20U.S.%20population%20is%20an%20estimated%20339.7%20million%20and%20the%20United%20Kingdom's%2068.1%20million.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20other%20words%2C%20while%20the%20UK's%20population%20was%20three%20times%20larger%20than%20the%20US's%20about%20225%20years%20ago%2C%20it%20is%20now%20only%20one-fifth%20of%20America's.%20Few%20countries%20have%20experienced%20such%20contrasting%20fortunes%20during%20this%20period%20except%20these%20two.%20At%20its%20peak%2C%20around%201922%2C%20the%20British%20Empire%20controlled%20a%20fourth%20of%20the%20world's%20land%20area.%20Its%20decline%20since%20then%20has%20been%20equally%20spectacular.%20The%20US%2C%20in%20contrast%2C%20has%20steadily%20grown%20stronger%20for%20well%20over%20a%20century.%20In%20fact%2C%20over%20the%20last%2050%20years%20alone%2C%20its%20economy%20has%20expanded%2027%20times%2C%20far%20outpacing%20the%2021-fold%20growth%20of%20the%20global%20economy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EPopulation%20And%20Growth%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELet's%20consider%20another%20data%20point.%20After%20decades%20of%20moderate%20growth%20or%20stagnation%2C%20%C2%A0while%20the%20world's%20population%20doubled%E2%80%94from%204%20billion%20to%208%20billion%E2%80%94between%201974%20and%202023%2C%20the%20global%20economy%20grew%20a%20staggering%2021%20times%20during%20the%20same%20period.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20point%20I'm%20making%20with%20these%20examples%20is%20simple%3A%20population%20growth%20has%20been%20one%20of%20the%20biggest%20drivers%20of%20economic%20growth%20across%20the%20world%20in%20recent%20years.%20This%20has%20been%20true%20for%20the%20US%2C%20Japan%2C%20South%20Korea%2C%20China%2C%20and%20now%20India.%20These%20countries%20have%20been%20dubbed%20%E2%80%9Cmiracle%20economies%E2%80%9D%20in%20different%20decades.%20While%20the%20US%20has%20been%20a%20consistent%20performer%20during%20periods%20of%20population%20explosion%2C%20Japan%2C%20South%20Korea%2C%20and%20China%20have%20had%20their%20occasional%20moments%20of%20glory.%20The%20key%20reason%20for%20this%20divergence%E2%80%94consistency%20in%20the%20US%20versus%20occasional%20bursts%20in%20other%20countries%E2%80%94lies%20in%20differences%20in%20population%20structure%20across%20these%20nations.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMy%20analysis%20of%20the%20economy%20and%20population%20dynamics%20of%20the%20four%20miracle%20economies%E2%80%94the%20US%2C%20Japan%2C%20South%20Korea%2C%20and%20China%E2%80%94shows%20that%20a%20median%20age%20of%2040%20or%20below%20is%20what%20drives%20economic%20growth.%20Once%20this%20threshold%20is%20surpassed%2C%20a%20pronounced%20decline%20begins.%20According%20to%20authoritative%20projections%2C%20India%20is%20expected%20to%20cross%20this%20threshold%20between%202055%20and%202060.%20Therefore%2C%20India%20has%20a%20limited%20window%20of%2030-35%20years%20to%20capitalise%20on%20its%20youthful%20demographic.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EGreying%2C%20Slowing%20Japan%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELet's%20take%20Japan%20as%20an%20example%20to%20understand%20why%20keeping%20the%20median%20age%20below%2040%20is%20crucial.%20Japan%20crossed%20this%20threshold%20in%202000%2C%20with%20its%20median%20age%20reaching%2040.7%20years.%20At%20that%20time%2C%20the%20size%20of%20the%20country's%20economy%20was%20%244.9%20trillion.%20In%202023%2C%20while%20the%20median%20age%20climbed%20to%2049.7%2C%20the%20size%20of%20its%20economy%20shrunk%20to%20%244%20trillion.%20This%20is%20why%20Japan%20is%20often%20cited%20as%20a%20classic%20case%20of%20%E2%80%9Cshrinkonomics%E2%80%9D%2C%20that%20is%2C%20a%20country%20that%20is%20shrinking%20on%20all%20fronts.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELet's%20look%20at%20China%2C%20another%20miracle%20economy%20that%20has%20experienced%20gravity-defying%20growth%20since%20the%201990s.%20Its%20median%20age%20was%2023.7%20years%20in%201990%2C%20and%20the%20size%20of%20its%20economy%20was%20a%20modest%20%24396%20billion.%20Today%2C%20its%20median%20age%20is%20likely%20to%20have%20surpassed%2040%2C%20and%20the%20size%20of%20its%20economy%20has%20soared%20to%20a%20staggering%20%2419.5%20trillion.%20In%20other%20words%2C%20before%20it%20began%20to%20grey%2C%20China's%20economy%20grew%2043%20times%20in%2035%20years.%20However%2C%20even%20before%20its%20median%20age%20crossed%20the%20threshold%20of%2040%2C%20the%20headlines%20coming%20out%20of%20China%20in%20recent%20years%20(even%20before%20the%20COVID-19%20pandemic%20broke%20out)%20have%20indicated%20that%20its%20economy%20is%20struggling%20on%20many%20fronts.%20The%20ageing%20population%20has%20put%20a%20decisive%20brake%20on%20the%20country's%20economic%20expansion.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EAmerica's%20Steady%20Age%20Profile%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20consider%20a%20country%20that%20has%20kept%20growing%20while%20managing%20its%20age%20profile%20for%20decades%3A%20the%20US.%20Its%20median%20age%20reached%2030%20in%201980%2C%20which%20was%20higher%20than%20India's%20current%20median%20age.%20While%20the%20US%20median%20age%20has%20since%20climbed%20to%2038.9%20after%2043%20years%2C%20India%20is%20unlikely%20to%20have%20the%20same%20luxury%20for%20an%20extended%20period.%20The%20reason%20the%20US%20has%20managed%20to%20keep%20its%20age%20profile%20relatively%20young%2C%20despite%20a%20significant%20dip%20in%20its%20fertility%20rate%20after%20the%201970s%2C%20is%20its%20liberal%20immigration%20policy.%20According%20to%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pewresearch.org%2Fshort-reads%2F2024%2F09%2F27%2Fkey-findings-about-us-immigrants%2F%23%3A~%3Atext%3DIn%25201970%252C%2520the%2520number%2520of%2Cincrease%2520from%25204.7%2525%2520in%25201970%5C%22%3EPew%20Research%20report%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%E2%80%9Cin%201970%2C%20the%20number%20of%20immigrants%20living%20in%20the%20U.S.%20was%20about%20a%20fifth%20of%20what%20it%20is%20today.%20Growth%20of%20this%20population%20accelerated%20after%20Congress%20made%20changes%20to%20U.S.%20immigration%20laws%20in%201965.%20Immigrants%20today%20account%20for%2014.3%25%20of%20the%20U.S.%20population%2C%20a%20roughly%20threefold%20increase%20from%204.7%25%20in%201970.%20The%20immigrant%20share%20of%20the%20population%20today%20is%20the%20highest%20since%201910%20but%20remains%20below%20the%20record%2014.8%25%20in%201890.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EIndia's%20Small%20Window%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%20would%20be%20well-served%20by%20adopting%20its%20own%20version%20of%20the%20approach%20the%20US%20has%20followed%20over%20the%20years.%20While%20India%20cannot%20afford%20to%20be%20liberal%20with%20immigration%20from%20other%20countries%2C%20it%20could%20implement%20policies%20that%20facilitate%20large-scale%20internal%20migration.%20The%20median%20age%20in%20southern%20states%20is%2032%20and%20older%2C%20while%20in%20states%20like%20Bihar%2C%20Uttar%20Pradesh%2C%20Madhya%20Pradesh%2C%20Rajasthan%2C%20Chhattisgarh%2C%20and%20Jharkhand%2C%20it%20ranges%20from%2022%20to%2026.%20Promoting%20liberal%20internal%20migration%20could%20help%20ensure%20a%20younger%20population%20profile%20across%20all%20states%2C%20boosting%20growth%20nationwide.%20This%20approach%20could%20help%20India%20make%20the%20most%20of%20its%20limited%20window%20before%20an%20ageing%20population%20begins%20to%20overwhelm%20the%20system.%20That%20is%20the%20only%20option.%20Otherwise%2C%20we%20will%20grey%20before%20we%20grow%20to%20our%20full%20potential.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E(The%20author%20is%20Consulting%20Editor%2C%20NDTV)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDisclaimer%3A%20These%20are%20the%20personal%20opinions%20of%20the%20author%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1737105300000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2019-03%2Fu6env2p_jobs-unemployment-reuters-_625x300_13_March_19.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Findia-must-act-fast-or-risk-losing-its-hr-advantage-7494563%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22My%20analysis%20of%20four%20miracle%20economies-the%20US%2C%20Japan%2C%20South%20Korea%2C%20and%20China-shows%20that%20a%20median%20age%20of%2040%20or%20below%20is%20what%20drives%20economic%20growth.%20According%20to%20projections%2C%20India%20is%20expected%20to%20cross%20this%20threshold%20between%202055%20and%202060%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Findia-must-act-fast-or-risk-losing-its-hr-advantage-7494563%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22What%20does%20the%20future%20hold%20for%20North%20Korean%20POWs%20in%20Ukraine%3F%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1737105185000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-117328611%2Cimgsize-62456.cms%2