%20consumption.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%20class%3D%5C%22twitter-tweet%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%20lang%3D%5C%22en%5C%22%3EWe%20are%20all%20proud%20of%20the%20efforts%20of%20all%20Government%20employees%2C%20who%20work%20to%20build%20a%20Viksit%20Bharat.%20The%20Cabinet's%20decision%20on%20the%208th%20Pay%20Commission%20will%20improve%20quality%20of%20life%20and%20give%20a%20boost%20to%20consumption.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ft.co%2F4DCa5skxNG%5C%22%3Ehttps%3A%2F%2Ft.co%2F4DCa5skxNG%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%E2%80%94%20Narendra%20Modi%20(%40narendramodi)%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fnarendramodi%2Fstatus%2F1879893038039973999%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3EJanuary%2016%2C%202025%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%5Cn%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cbr%3E%5CnThe%20announcement%20comes%20months%20after%20the%20dearness%20allowance%20(DA)%20for%20central%20government%20employees%20crossed%2050%25%20of%20their%20basic%20salary.%20Starting%20July%201%2C%202024%2C%20both%20central%20government%20employees%20and%20pensioners%20began%20receiving%2053%25%20of%20their%20basic%20pay%20as%20DA%2Frelief%2C%20with%20the%20next%20revision%20set%20for%20January%202025.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20central%20government%20employees%20expect%20from%20the%208th%20Pay%20Commission%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20salary%20structure%20currently%20in%20place%20follows%20the%20recommendations%20made%20by%20the%207th%20Pay%20Commission%2C%20which%20came%20into%20effect%20on%20January%201%2C%202016.%20With%20the%20formation%20of%20the%208th%20Pay%20Commission%2C%20the%20structure%20is%20set%20for%20revision.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20exact%20percentage%20of%20salary%20hike%20has%20not%20been%20disclosed%2C%20reports%20suggest%20that%20the%20fitment%20factor%20%E2%80%94%20the%20key%20multiplier%20used%20to%20determine%20salaries%20and%20pensions%20%E2%80%94%20could%20see%20a%20rise%20from%202.57%20to%202.86.%20If%20this%20occurs%2C%20the%20minimum%20basic%20salary%20for%20government%20employees%20could%20increase%20significantly%2C%20rising%20from%20Rs%2018%2C000%20to%20Rs%2051%2C480.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EUnderstanding%20fitment%20factor%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20fitment%20factor%20is%20an%20important%20element%20used%20in%20calculating%20the%20revised%20salary%20and%20pension%20amounts%20for%20central%20government%20employees.%20It%20serves%20as%20a%20multiplication%20coefficient%2C%20which%20adjusts%20the%20pay%20scale%20in%20accordance%20with%20the%20new%20commission's%20recommendations.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUnder%20the%207th%20Pay%20Commission%2C%20the%20fitment%20factor%20was%202.57%2C%20which%20led%20to%20an%20increase%20in%20the%20minimum%20basic%20salary%20of%20central%20government%20employees%20from%20Rs%207%2C000%20under%20the%206th%20Pay%20Commission%20to%20Rs%2018%2C000.%20The%20basic%20salary%20excludes%20perks%2C%20allowances%2C%20and%20performance%20pay.%20When%20dearness%20allowance%20(DA)%2C%20house%20rent%20allowance%20(HRA)%2C%20transport%20allowance%20(TA)%2C%20and%20other%20benefits%20are%20factored%20in%2C%20the%20total%20minimum%20salary%20went%20up%20to%20Rs%2036%2C020%20per%20month%20under%20the%207th%20Pay%20Commission.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20depending%20on%20the%20final%20directives%20from%20the%208th%20Pay%20Commission%2C%20various%20allowances%20may%20undergo%20changes.%20This%20revision%20is%20expected%20to%20substantially%20increase%20the%20remuneration%20of%20central%20government%20employees.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1737104340000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2020-09%2Fcqjbnl_rupee-generic_625x300_20_September_20.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fbusiness-news%2F8th-pay-commission-what-salary-hike-central-employees-can-expect-7494483%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20Union%20Cabinet%2C%20led%20by%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%2C%20approved%20the%20formation%20of%20the%208th%20Pa