%20from%20Gaza%20attacked%20Israel%20on%20a%20Jewish%20holiday.%20They%20went%20about%20indiscriminately%20shooting%20and%20kidnapping%20unsuspecting%20civilians%20and%20some%20soldiers.%20The%20worst%20attack%20was%20on%20a%20music%20festival%20where%20hundreds%20of%20young%20Israelis%20were%20partying.%20All%20of%20it%20streamed%20live%20by%20the%20attackers'%20body-mounted%20cameras.%20By%20the%20time%20Israeli%20forces%20took%20out%20the%20last%20gunmen%2C%20the%20body%20count%20had%20topped%201%2C200.%20Over%20250%20hostages%20were%20carried%20across%20to%20Gaza%20to%20be%20stashed%20away%20in%20a%20subterranean%20maze%20where%20they%20remained%20undiscovered%20even%20after%20the%20whole%20house%20was%20burnt%20down.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPerhaps%20the%20most%20dramatic%20and%20horrific%20cross-border%20assault%20on%20any%20country%20since%20the%20Mumbai%20terror%20attacks%20of%202008%2C%20it%20triggered%20such%20a%20display%20of%20overwhelming%20force%20that%20it%20left%20the%20world%20aghast.%20The%20shockwaves%20have%20left%20the%20regional%20map%20perceptibly%20different.%20It%20has%20riven%20apart%20communities%20and%20split%20institutions.%20The%20scars%20run%20so%20deep%20that%20they%20will%20not%20heal%20in%20a%20very%20long%20time.%20It%20has%20also%20laid%20bare%20the%20remarkable%20pragmatism%20bordering%20on%20chutzpah%20of%20the%20Arab%20nations.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EReduced%20To%20Rubble%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20multiple%20reports%2C%20nearly%2046%2C000%20Gazans%2C%20a%20substantial%20number%20of%20them%20women%20and%20children%2C%20have%20perished%20in%20the%2015-month%20war.%20Most%20of%20Gaza%20has%20been%20flattened%20and%20rendered%20uninhabitable.%20Israel%20is%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.middleeastmonitor.com%2F20250113-tens-of-millions-of-tonnes-of-rubble-left-in-gaza-as-homes-have-been-flattened-report-reveals%2F%5C%22%3Eestimated%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20have%20demolished%20over%201%2C61%2C600%20homes%20and%20damaged%201%2C94%2C000%20other%20civil%20structures.%20More%20than%201.9%20million%20of%20the%202.2%20million%20Gazans%20have%20become%20refugees%2C%20most%20of%20them%20corralled%20into%20a%20tiny%20corner%20in%20the%20north%20of%20the%20Strip.%20More%20than%201%2C000%20medical%20facilities%20have%20been%20destroyed%3B%20Rafah%20does%20not%20have%20a%20single%20hospital.%20The%20economic%20loss%20is%20estimated%20at%20%2437%20billion.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHamas%20was%20decapitated%20when%20its%20political%20leader%20Ismail%20Haniyeh%20was%20assassinated%20in%20Tehran%2C%20where%20he%20had%20gone%20to%20attend%20the%20inauguration%20ceremony%20for%20Iranian%20President%20Masoud%20Pezeshkian.%20Its%20director%20of%20war%2C%20Yahya%20Sinwar%2C%20was%20killed%20in%20Gaza%20last%20year%2C%20just%20after%20the%20first%20anniversary%20of%20the%20Hamas%20attack.%20A%20video%20of%20a%20dying%20Sinwar%20defiantly%20throwing%20a%20piece%20of%20wood%20at%20an%20Israeli%20military%20drone%20indicated%20that%20Hamas%20would%20not%20back%20down%20despite%20the%20carnage.%20By%20the%20end%20of%202024%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.middleeastmonitor.com%2F20250111-israels-gaza-war-costs-exceed-67b-report%2F%5C%22%3EIsrael%20had%20spent%3C%2Fa%3E%20over%20%2467%20billion%20on%20war.%20It%20had%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwatson.brown.edu%2Fcostsofwar%2Fpapers%2F2024%2FUSspendingIsrael%5C%22%3Ecost%20the%20United%20States%3C%2Fa%3E%20nearly%20%2423%20billion%20until%20September%202024.%20Yet%2C%20about%20a%20hundred%20Israelis%20remain%20hostages%20somewhere%20in%20the%20ruins%2C%20or%2C%20more%20likely%2C%20under%20the%20ground.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Deal%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESo%2C%20what%20is%20the%20new%20acceptable%20middle%20ground%20in%20the%20new%20deal%20that%20the%20failed%20talks%20since%20the%20first%20successful%20one%20in%20November%20of%202023%20could%20not%20find%3F%20After%20all%2C%20the%20original%20objective%20of%20the%20war%E2%80%94freeing%20hostages%E2%80%94was%20not%20achieved.%20Not%20only%20that%2C%20Israel%20will%20release%20over%201%2C000%20Palestinians%2C%20including%20those%20arrested%20after%20October%207%20and%20presumably%20Hamas%20fighters%2C%20in%20a%20prisoner%20exchange.%20That%20means%20while%20thousands%20of%20innocent%20Gazans%2C%20including%20women%20and%20children%2C%20paid%20for%20the%20Hamas%20attack%20with%20their%20lives%2C%20its%20fighters%20may%20yet%20return%2C%20alive%2C%20prison-hardened%2C%20and%20ready%20to%20fight%20another%20day.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20December%2020%2C%202024%2C%20American%20journalist%20Seymour%20Hersh%E2%80%94famous%20for%20blowing%20the%20lid%20off%20a%20cover-up%20of%20a%20massacre%20of%20the%20villagers%20of%20My%20Lai%20in%20Vietnam%20by%20US%20troops%20in%20the%201960s%E2%80%94wrote%20that%20an%20Israel-Hamas%20ceasefire%20deal%20was%20in%20the%20works.%20The%20contours%20of%20the%20just-announced%20deal%20are%20nearly%20identical%20to%20that%20in%20his%20report.%20%C2%A0One%20crucial%20piece%20of%20information%2C%20which%20was%20not%20in%20the%20deal%20made%20public%20but%20available%20in%20Hersh's%20Israeli%20source-based%20account%2C%20was%20the%20role%20of%20Saudi%20Arabia%20and%20the%20quid%20pro%20quos.%20Hersh%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fseymourhersh.substack.com%2Fp%2Fthe-new-ceasefire-equation%3Futm_source%3Dpost-email-title%26publication_id%3D1377040%26post_id%3D153387346%26utm_campaign%3Demail-post-title%26isFreemail%3Dfalse%26r%3D7erut%26triedRedirect%3Dtrue%26utm_medium%3Demail%5C%22%3Ewrote%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20as%20per%20the%20deal%E2%80%94%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Fworld%2Fmiddle-east%2Fhow-months-of-geopolitical-upheaval-paved-way-for-gaza-cease-fire-52a285d6%3Fmod%3Dhp_lead_pos1%5C%22%3Ereportedly%20made%20possible%3C%2Fa%3E%20after%20incoming%20US%20President%20Donald%20Trump%20shook%20his%20fist%20at%20the%20belligerent%20Israel%20Pri